:: Gwylan Walk School Robin
<<set $outside to 1>><<set $location to "town">><<effects>>
<<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set _robin to statusCheck("Robin")>><<set _gwylan to [0, 1].includes($phase) ? "gwylan" : "none">><<set _robin to $robin_in_cafe ? "robin" : "none">>

<span class="red">ERROR: Unfinished scene. You're not supposed to get here. Please report this bug.</span>
<br><br>

<<schoolWalkChat _gwylan _robin>>

You soon arrive at the front gates.
<<if C.npc.Gwylan.dom gte random(10, 200) and [0, 1].includes($phase)>>
	Gwylan suddenly grows a mischievous grin.
	<br><br>

	Just before you walk through, <<he>> pulls you and Robin into a big hug.
	"Have a good day at school, dears!" <<he>> says far too loudly. Loud enough for several students to turn and look at you.
	<<He>> rubs <<his>> face up against yours and makes a big show of it. <<stress 5>><<gstress>>
	<br><br>

	<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning") and $gwylan.robin gte 20>>
		<<He>> finishes it off with an exaggerated kiss to Robin's cheek, and then yours. "Mwah! Mmmmmwah!" You hear laughter from the other students.
		<<He>> finally releases you, giving you a wink before waving you off.
	<<else>>
		<<He>> releases you after a moment, and winks before waving you off.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<<if $cool gte 160>>
		You expect to never hear the end of this as some of your friends approach you. "I thought you two lived at the orphanage," one says.
		"I didn't think your <<if $pronoun is "m">>dad<<else>>mum<</if>> would be so hot," another says. "<<He>> doesn't even look the age. Wait, are you two siblings?"
		<br><br>

		Robin's face turns bright red, and they don't let <<nnpc_him "Robin">> get a word in about it. You're embarrassed too, but at least you're not being made fun of. <<stress 3>><<trauma -2>><<npcincr Robin dom -5>><<gstress>><<ltrauma>><<lldom "Robin">>
	<<else>>
		You can already hear some of the jokes about your "<<father>>" at your expense. <<status -1>><<lcool>><<npcincr Robin dom -1>><<ldom "Robin">>
	<</if>>
<<elseif [0, 1].includes($phase)>>
	<<He>> wishes you and Robin a good day at school and waves you both goodbye.
<</if>>
<br><br>

Robin walks ahead, wanting to get a head start on studying.
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|School Front Courtyard]]>><<endevent>><</link>>
