:: Gwylan Ocean Breeze Ice Cream
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $phase is 0>>
	You find Gwylan crouched in front of the <<person2>><<personsimple>>. <<person1>><<He>> pulls out a handkerchief and wipes away the <<person2>><<personsimple>>'s tears.
	<br><br>

	"You poor thing," <<person1>><<he>> says. "That looked like a nice ice cream. Was it a triple scoop?"
	<br><br>

	The <<person2>><<personsimple>> sniffs, and nods. Gwylan pats <<him>> on the head.
	<br><br>

	<<person1>><<He>> reaches behind the <<person2>><<personsimple>>'s ear and pulls out a large banknote. The <<personsimple>> stops crying. "Here, take this and buy yourself an even better one."
	<br><br>

	<<person1>><<He>> closes the <<person2>><<personsimple>>'s fist around the money. The <<personsimple>> stares at Gwylan. "This... this is so much money," <<he>> says. <<He>> gets to <<his>> feet with a watery smile.
	<<person1>>"<<print either("Thank you <<if $pronoun is 'm'>>mister<<else>>miss<</if>>!", "Yippee!", "You're the best!", "You're super nice, like my <<print either('dad', 'mum')>>.", "I will! Thank you.", "Th-thank you...", "You're really kind.", "<<print either('Father', 'Mother')>> told me not to talk to strangers, but... you seem alright!", "You're like, the coolest grown-up ever!", "Thank you. I... I like your hat.", "I'm gonna buy my <<print either('friend', 'brother', 'sister')>> one too!")>>"
	<<person2>><<He>> beams, and runs off in the direction of the boardwalk.
	<br><br>

	As Gwylan watches <<him>> go, you notice an expression on <<person1>><<his>> face so <<if $pronoun is "m">>fatherly<<else>>motherly<</if>> that you feel a tug in your chest. <<if Object.values(V.children).length>>Your mind wanders to your own child<<if Object.values(V.children).length gte 2>>ren<</if>>. <</if>><<He>> motions you back to the balcony. You hasten to follow.
	<br><br>

	<<endevent>><<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
	<<gwylanOptions>>
<<else>>
	You watch as Gwylan rushes to the <<person2>><<personsimple>>. <<person1>><<He>> spends quite a bit of time chatting. By the time <<he>> gives the <<person2>><<personsimple>> a light push, <<person2>><<hes>> already giggling. Gwylan waves as <<he>> skips away.
	<br><br>

	<<person1>><<He>> makes <<his>> way back to the balcony. There's an expression on <<his>> face so <<if $pronoun is "m">>fatherly<<else>>motherly<</if>> that you feel a tug in your chest. <<if Object.values(V.children).length>>Your mind wanders to your own child<<if Object.values(V.children).length gte 2>>ren<</if>>. <</if>><<He>> leans against the railing again.
