:: Gwylan Talk Struggles Revenge
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $gwylan.triumph to "revenge">>
<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"I've been hurt," you say quietly. "I need to hurt them back."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"I've been beaten. Violated. Tortured." Your fists clench. "I'm going to give it all back, and more. So, so much more."
	<<default>>
		"I have to make my own justice," you say. "There's people that have wronged me. Hurt me. Violated me. They must face consequences."
<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan stares ahead. "I remember a time when I was so fiery. It only keeps you going for so long. Every fire burns up the air around it. Eventually, there won't be any air left for you to breathe. You'll burn out, or consume all the fuel.
What will be left at the end of that?" <<He>> looks back to you. <span class="red">"A pile of ashes."</span> <<He>> smiles. "Don't mistake my words. Wanting revenge is fine, but there must be more than that. It can't be all you live for."
<br><br>

<<He>> takes a deep breath, filling <<his>> lungs with the salty air. "I hope you know you're not alone in this fight of yours, either. I'll always be in your corner. If..." <<He>> pauses, trying to sort out <<his>> words.
"If you burnt out like that, if you got your revenge and then faded away, I'd miss what we have. <span class="pink">I'd miss you.</span>"
