	"I laugh with the sinners. The saints can cry me a river," you say. "I must have been put here for a reason. Maybe this is some divine punishment. Maybe this is Hell. I might as well enjoy it, since I can't leave anyways." <<trauma -3>><<ltrauma>>
	<br><br>

	Gwylan frowns. "It's comforting to think that way, isn't it? That you're part of the problem, so the problem won't still hurt you? If you look deeper, you'll see the truth. All this pleasure is temporary, and the cost is great."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> sighs. "Take care, little imp. I'd hate to see you pass through real Hell." <<He>> pauses, and smiles. "But if you do... I'll jump in and drag you back out. <span class="pink">I'd miss you too much otherwise.</span>"
<<elseif $auriga_scar>>
	"I saw something that I can't unsee," you start. "An eye in the blood moon. It was magnificent. It promised me things without words and left something on me. I want to see it again."
	<br><br>

	Gwylan winces. "Its promises are empty. As empty as you'll be when it's done with you. It won't comfort you, or fulfil you. It will <span class="red">devour</span> you. I hope you realise that before it's too late."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> sighs. "You aren't the first to think you'll be different, and you won't be the last. You'll end up in the Elk's gullet." <<He>> pauses, and smiles. "But in that case, I'll have to jump in and pull you back out. <span class="pink">I'd miss you too much otherwise.</span>"
<<else>>
	"It's not all that bad," you say. "I get my share of the pleasure. I might as well enjoy it, since I can't leave anyways."
	<br><br>

	Gwylan frowns. "I didn't take you for a hedonist. It's comforting to think that way, isn't it? That you're part of the problem, so the problem won't hurt you? If you look deeper, you'll see the truth. All this pleasure is temporary, and the cost is great."
	<br><br>

	<<He>> sighs. "Take care, dear. This is Hell, and slipping deeper is no way to live." <<He>> pauses, and smiles. "But if you do slip deeper, I'll jump in and drag you back out. <span class="pink">I'd miss you too much otherwise.</span>"
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<link [[Say nothing|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you'd miss Gwylan too|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Struggles Innocent
<<set $gwylan.triumph to "innocent">>
"I don't know what you mean. Is there anything particularly strange about what I've told you? Is getting all this attention not normal?"
<br><br>

Gwylan's eyes widen. "Oh, no. No no no, absolutely not." <<He>> starts shaking <<his>> head. "Meet me at the shop for the next ritual.
Your eyes need to be opened, dear, and soon. Otherwise you'll be swallowed, and never even see it coming. I can't allow that. <span class="pink">I'd miss you too much.</span>"
<br><br>

<<link [[Say nothing|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you'd miss Gwylan too|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Struggles Answers
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $gwylan.triumph to "curiosity">>
<<switch $speech_attitude>>
	<<case "meek">>
		"There's something going on. Something big," you say. "Bigger than me. I need to know why everything is the way it is here. Why we have to suffer like this."
	<<case "bratty">>
		"There's something rotten going on in this town," you say. "Anyone could tell you that, but so many people act like it's normal. Why? Why does it feel like there's a big secret that everyone's in on except me?"
	<<default>>
		"I have too many questions," you say. "Why is this town is like this? Why does everyone act like its normal? Why do we have to suffer the way we do?"
<</switch>>
<br><br>

Gwylan smiles sadly. "We have much in common. We're both far too curious for our own good. It's a dangerous thing, to poke one's nose into the bear's den like we do."
<br><br>

<<He>> places a hand on your shoulder. "I hope you continue returning here, to tell me what you've found. I promise you I'll keep remembering it all, so even if you never come back, these questions won't fade away in your absence.
Don't take that as an excuse to be reckless, though. If you ever stopped coming around, I'd miss our conversations. <span class="pink">I'd miss you.</span>"
<br><br>

<<link [[Say nothing|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you'd miss Gwylan too|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Struggles Unknown
<<set $gwylan.triumph to "unknown">>
"I..." you continue thinking, but nothing comes to mind. "I don't know. I just keep going."
<br><br>

Gwylan smiles patiently. "It's alright. Sometimes the sheer determination to keep going is enough, but not for long. Think on it some more. Find out what it is that you value, and cherish."
<br><br>

<<He>> pauses. "I cherish our conversations. The stories you entrust me with. I hope you find something worth holding on for soon, because <span class="pink">I'd miss you if you gave up and vanished on me.</span>"
<br><br>

<<link [[Say nothing|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you'd miss Gwylan too|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Struggles Desolate
<<set $gwylan.triumph to "desolate">>
"I... don't want to," you say. A lump forms in your throat. "I don't want to anymore. I just want to lie down and..."
<br><br>

Gwylan stands and pulls you into a tight hug. "You wouldn't be standing here if you truly wanted to give up. You're stronger than you know. Don't give up now. Not after coming so far." <<He>> pets the top of your head. <<trauma -2>><<stress -2>><<lstress>><<ltrauma>>
<br><br>

<<He>> gently turns your head to look to the sea. "It's so tempting, isn't it? To let the waves pull you under? To embrace oblivion? That wouldn't be the end. It would be too easy. As things are now, there is no bottom to reach."
<br><br>

<<He>> sits back down. "I don't want to see you break. I cherish our conversations. The stories you entrust me with. I hope you find something worth holding on for soon, because <span class="pink">I'd miss you if you gave up and vanished on me.</span>"
<br><br>

<<link [[Say nothing|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say you'd miss Gwylan too|Gwylan Talk Struggles 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Talk Struggles 2
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>><<set $daily.gwylan.cafeSkip to true>><<set $daily.gwylan.locked to true>>
<<if $phase is 2>>
	/* player would miss Gwylan */
	Gwylan smiles again. "That's an unfortunate burden to carry, but... thank you."
<<elseif $phase is 3>>
	/* player would not miss Gwylan */
	Gwylan smiles again. "Good. Let your heart remain unburdened."
<<elseif $phase is 4>>
	/* player says they're holding on for Gwylan */
	<<set $gwylan.triumph to "Gwylan">>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>
			"I was... talking about you," you say shyly.
		<<case "bratty">>
			"I know you'd miss me, you were the one I was talking about," you say.
		<<default>>
			"I was talking about you," you say.
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	Gwylan stares at you, <<his>> expression entirely neutral. "That's nonsense. You hardly know me." <<He>> waves off your comment.
	<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion gte 1>>
		"It's just the side effects of the hypnosis talking."
	<</if>>
<</if>>
<<His>> eyes get cloudy and dim as <<he>> watches the waves. "I'm sorry, but I'd like to be alone for a little while. I'll see you soon, though? I could use your help at the shop again, when the time comes."
<br><br>

<<if $location is "cafe" and !(between($chef_state, 7, 8) and $chef_rework lte 30)>>
	You turn to leave once again, returning to the inside of the cafe.
<<else>>
	You turn to leave again, returning to Cliff street.
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<set $gwylan.sea++>>

<<if hasSharpSenses("hearing")>>
	<span class="teal">Your <<= hasSharpSenses("hearing")>> catch Gwylan's whispering.</span> <<He>> must think you're out of earshot. You listen in.
	<br><br>

	"<<pShes>> ready. I'm sure of it.<br>
	The faintest rumble answers <<him>>.<br>
	<<if $auriga_scar>>
		"Yes, even with the scar. <<pShes>> not the only one so marked."
	<<else>>
		"Don't 'I told you so' me, I needed to be sure."<br>
	<</if>>
	The waves crash against the shoreline.<br>
	"Yes, <span class="blue">next time</span>, I promise."
	<br><br>

	You wonder who <<hes>> talking to.
<<else>>
	A shiver runs down your spine. You hear Gwylan whispering, but it's too faint to make out. You try to listen, but only manage to catch the end of it.
	<br><br>

	"<span class="blue">Next time</span>, I promise."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<set $daily.gwylan.preventProgress to true>>

<<if $location is "cafe" and !(between($chef_state, 7, 8) and $chef_rework lte 30)>>
	<<if $daily.robin_in_cafe and Time.schoolDay>>
