:: Gwylan Talk Brown Fox Mask
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $brownFoxMaskTalk to true>>
"Is the brown fox mask really for concealing your identity? Do they really not know who you are by now?"
<br><br>

<<He>> giggles. "It's easier if they suspect some masked vigilante. If they started suspecting otherwise..." <<he>> pauses. "They might start making some connections. Dangerous ones."
<br><br>

"So why a fox mask specifically?" you ask.
<br><br>

<<He>> looks down. "It's symbolic. I want them to see the face of their victims biting back." <<He>> rubs the cheek of the mask.
"When I wear this, I'm not Gwylan. I'm every single victim of the elks and hounds. I'm their vengeance." <<His>> hands clench slightly. "No one else will give it to them. The Cloister will just make them suffer more, use them as... vessels.
Us foxes only have each other."
<br><br>

<<He>> puts the mask on. "That's what the brown fox symbolises."
<<if $avery_fate is "ascended">>
	<<He>> looks away, concealing a frown. "I don't blame you for what happened. I know how hard it can be to say no, to keep struggling when it only brings more bruises.
	It isn't too late, but the path ahead is dark, so expect to find dark things. No matter what, us foxes need to look out for each other."
<<elseif $avery_mansion.fox.progress gte 12 or $gwylanSeen.includes("ritual_sex")>>
	<<He>> looks away, and you catch the faintest blush beneath <<his>> mask. "I'm glad you're here with me, <<pcpetname "Gwylan" "name">>. I've worked alone for far too long." <<npcincr Gwylan dom 1>><<gyearning>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

