:: Gwylan Yearning Climb
<<effects>>
You start to climb the stairs. After nine steps, you realise that the staircase is curved.
<br><br>

You rub your eyes. You can still see a light straight ahead, but there should be a wall there.
You reach forward, and feel smooth glass. There must be a mirror on the wall, reflecting the light from above.
<br><br>

You continue up, feeling your way along the wall. Not being able to see in front of or behind you makes you nervous and claustrophobic. <<stress 3>><<gstress>>
<br><br>

<<silently>><<dancedifficulty 300 800>><</silently>>
<span class="red">You trip on the next step.</span>
<<if $danceSuccess>>
	Luckily, <span class="green">you don't need your eyes to recover from a stumble.</span> You have experience thanks to all the dancing you've done. You take two controlled steps down, and stop your momentum.
<<else>>
	<span class="red">You flail blindly,</span> and grab onto something. It's large and solid. You're almost certain whatever it is wasn't there before, because it's right behind where you were standing. <<stress 9>><<ggstress>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

You orient yourself, and start to shimmy along the wall again. There's something wrong, though. <span class="blue">The wall's curve seems to be going in the opposite direction.</span> You're moving down now instead, as if the stairs were suddenly mirrored.
<br><br>

<<link [[Turn around and make sure you're going up|Gwylan Yearning Ascend]]>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Keep going down|Gwylan Yearning Descend]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Gwylan Yearning Descend
<<effects>>
You keep going down.
<br><br>

You exit in far fewer steps than it took you to get to where you were, and emerge in an unfamiliar room. Dim embers glow in an old furnace. It's just bright enough that you can tell it's a kitchen of some kind.
That's your best guess, at least, with all the cutlery hanging around you.
<br><br>

There's another door here, and it's already open. You peek inside, and see <span class="red">three glowing eyes staring back at you</span>. <<stress 12>><<ggstress>>
<br><br>

You step back on instinct, but fall and land on your bottom. The door creaks open further.
<br><br>

The glow vanishes as more light enters the room beyond. On the wall straight ahead is an elk's skull, fashioned into a mask. Each of its antlers ends in three prongs.
<br><br>

Directly below it is a brown fox mask with a third eye on its forehead. Next to it, clasped to the wall, is a blade with a sudden curve near the end. It looks like a billhook, but its handle is broken. It reflects the dim light.
<br><br>

All around them are charms made of twigs, as well as countless hanging outfits that you've never seen in the main part of the shop. Many of them look ceremonial.
There's nothing else in the room, so you turn around and head back up the stairs.
<br><br>

You manage to avoid tripping this time. After a long climb, your foot comes down hard, expecting another step where there is none. You're on a level surface. There's a bit of light here, creeping through the edges of a doorframe.
<br><br>

<<link [[Enter|Gwylan Yearning Door]]>><<set $phase to 0>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Knock first|Gwylan Yearning Door]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
