<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> paces back and forth. "This isn't a path we can walk together, dear. One day, you won't come back. Or, you'll come around, and I won't be here anymore."
<<He>> takes a deep breath, and snaps <<his>> fingers. "Just like that. Gone. We'll move on and forget. It's easier to do that if things remain simple between us."

<<His>> head tilts slightly. "That's only if we're lucky, though. The more likely outcome is one of us getting chewed up into something unrecognisable.
Then we can't move on. We'll be stuck trying to piece each other back together. Forever. That's worse than death."
<br><br>

<<His>> voice is monotone as <<he>> looks you in the eyes. "I called you here because I want you to tell me that your kiss meant nothing.
I want you to tell me that it was just done in the heat of passion, and that you and I are not, and will never be, more than friends."
