<</if>>
You aren't ready for forever. You're barely ready for right now."
<br><br>

<<He>> stops, and sighs. <<He>> takes another step towards you. "No. It isn't you. If one of a mated pair meets an early end, especially before they have kits, <span class="red">it's not uncommon for the other to die of a broken heart</span>."
<br><br>

Another step, and <<he>> puts a finger under your chin. "<span class="purple">Mine is already broken,</span> because I was never allowed what I craved. What I <i>needed</i>.
Worse, it was dangled in front of me like the sweetest nectar, before being ripped away, over and over, each time worse than the last. Did you think you were my first lay? My first friend?
Did you think you would be my first loss? Do you think yours are the first stories and memories I have to carry forever?" <<His>> voice trembles.
<br><br>

"I have nothing to give you. This can't even begin, nevermind end. Do you understand? <span class="red">I <i>can't</i> let myself go through this again.</span>"
<br><br>

<<He>> takes a step back, only now realising that <<hes>> backed you into the corner. "I'm sorry. This is my fault to begin with. The hypnosis, over time, can have effects like this.
I told you I didn't want things to change between us. You're my friend. I don't want to lose you just because of some fake, hypnosis-induced puppy love. So, please. Tell me it meant nothing and mean it, so we can go back to the way things were."
